snippet.textDisplay:
Very timely video. I just wrote to PEET'S coffee to ask why, as a lactose intolerant person, they charge me
$.0.70 cents more for my almond milk cappuccino. After watching this video, I understand. their reply:
""...non-dairy alternatives are more of a premium product than our standard milk.  Since these are more premium and are specialty formulated for steaming they are more expensive and we do have to charge more for them.  I do understand your frustrations and have shared this with our retail team.". 
Still hate to pay more, so will probably switch to espresso shots.
snippet.textOriginal:
Very timely video. I just wrote to PEET'S coffee to ask why, as a lactose intolerant person, they charge me 
$.0.70 cents more for my almond milk cappuccino. After watching this video, I understand. their reply: 
""...non-dairy alternatives are more of a premium product than our standard milk.  Since these are more premium and are specialty formulated for steaming they are more expensive and we do have to charge more for them.  I do understand your frustrations and have shared this with our retail team.". 
Still hate to pay more, so will probably switch to espresso shots.
